org.orgName: United States District Court For The Western District of Washington Northern Division

div1.p: In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington. Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Chas. Jackson, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
div1.ab:
Filed in the United States District Court
Western District of Washington
Northern Division
Feb 5 1919
F. M. Harsberger, Clerk
By S. E. Leitch Deputy
div1.p: The above entitled matter having come regularly on for hearing on the 2d day of December, 1918, on the petition for a Writ of Habeas Corpus, the Writ of Habeas Corpus and respondent's return thereto, and the Court having heard arguments of counsel and being fully advised in the premises, it is hereby
ORDERED, That the said Writ be and the same is hereby denied with costs to petitioner, and the petitioner remanded to the custody of the Commissioner of Immigration.
Done in open court this 5 day of February, A. D. 1919.

closer.signed:
Jeremiah Neterer
United States District Judge
